3.30	School_of_Quietude	Ron Silliman	Ron Silliman (born 5 August 1946 in Pasco, Washington) is an American poet. He has written and edited over 30 books, and has had his poetry and criticism translated into 12 languages. He is often associated with language poetry. Between 1979 and 2004, Silliman wrote a single poem, The Alphabet. He has now begun writing a new poem, Universe, the first section of which appears to be called Revelator.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/93/Ron_Silliman.jpg/220px-Ron_Silliman.jpg
